var PI = 3.14;
PI = 42; // stop me from doing this!

/* Write an ES2015 Version */
const PI =3.14;


What is the difference between var and let?
You can redeclare or reassign var. You can't redeclare using let. Let creates a block scope.  

What is the difference between var and const?
You can redeclare or reassign var. You can't reassign or redeclare const. Const creates a block scope.  

What is the difference between let and const?
You can reassign let but not redeclare it. You can't reassign or redeclare const. 

What is hoisting?
It is how we explain how the JS compiler works. Variables are hoisted to the top of the scope they are declared in. 
